South Africa's most successful DJ took home the award for the best dance/electronic album at the 64th Grammy awards on Monday morning in Los Angeles. Black Coffee, whose real name is Nathi Maphumulo, won for his album titled-Subconsciously. The renowned music producer is the first South African to be nominated and win in the category. DJ Black Coffee has thanked his fans for their support as they gathered at OR Tambo International Airport. Maphumulo touched down on home soil on Tuesday night, receiving a hero's welcome from government officials, family members and hundreds of fans.
